<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="189" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,911,1262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,210,912,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[219,422,911,938]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindleyana">
<emphasis box="[219,422,911,938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Cassia lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the collection 
<emphasis box="[871,1017,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1160,911,937]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but the only information contained in the original description for typification purposes is plants from the “Organ Mountains, hab. in woods, common”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G." box="[258,493,983,1010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" pagination="1 - 528" refId="ref4953" refString="Bentham, G. (1870) Leguminosae II. Et III. Swartzieae, Caesalpinieae, Mimoseae. In: Martius, K. F. P. von, Eichler, A. W. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora Brasiliensis. vol. XV, Pars II, Fasc. 50. Lipsiae, Londinensis., pp. 1 - 528." type="book chapter" year="1870">Bentham (1870: 123)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName box="[624,772,983,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindleyana">
<emphasis box="[624,772,983,1010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1042,983,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multijuga">
<emphasis box="[905,1042,983,1010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. multijuga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the collection 
<emphasis box="[1302,1444,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[136,461,1019,1046]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" pagination="1 - 454" refId="ref5268" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 454." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982: 498)</bibRefCitation>
changed the status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Gardner" box="[705,1016,1019,1046]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="multijuga" variety="lindleyana">
<emphasis box="[705,843,1019,1046]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. multijuga</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[898,1016,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the subspecies level, and mistakenly indicated the specimen of the collection 
<emphasis box="[599,745,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[828,929,1055,1081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">holotype</typeStatus>
, under barcode K000555411, deposited at the Kew Herbarium (K). The species protologue, however, does not indicate where the 
<typeStatus box="[1072,1170,1091,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">holotype</typeStatus>
was deposited, and there is no indication that the specimen suggested by those authors was the material used by Gardner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,911,1262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
