from the collection 
<emphasis box="[693,836,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFE8FF549C1CFD0D069C:8E9CF9A8FFC9FFE8FD699AF8FCEE06D4" box="[693,788,1163,1189]" country="Brazil" name="Gardner" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner</location>
367
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[902,973,1163,1189]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and designate here the specimen deposited at K, under barcode K000555411 as the 
<typeStatus box="[589,692,1199,1225]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">lectotype</typeStatus>
as it is well preserved, and also because (according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Thiers, B." box="[1307,1443,1199,1226]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" refId="ref6117" refString="Thiers, B. (2021) Index Herbariorum: a global directory of public herbaria and associated staff. New York Botanical Garden's Virtual Herbarium, New York. Available from: http: // sweetgum. nybg. org / ih / (accessed 25 July 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Thiers 2021</bibRefCitation>
) the Kew Herbarium houses Gardner’s main collections
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
